    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Rear Cover - Installation</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s26513.3">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc id="s26513.3.1" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="8">
            <title>Rear Cover</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, before installing the rear cover, replace dowel sleeves in crankcase
                        if damaged or missing.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="e3001417" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06043.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Installing the rear cover gasket (typical)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new rear cover gasket onto rear cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3001414" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06022.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Application of sealant (typical)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply Liquid Gasket (RTV) at two locations, where the crankcase and lower crankcase
                    join. See
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_293.xml" xrefid="E30014C">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not allow Liquid Gasket (RTV) to set longer than 10 minutes prior
                        to tightening joint.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="e3001415" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06023.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Applying Liquid Gasket (RTV) under the high-pressure pump cover (typical)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply a small amount of Liquid Gasket (RTV) under the high-pressure pump cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not allow Liquid Gasket (RTV) to set longer than 10 minutes prior
                        to tightening joint.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="e3001416" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06024.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Applying oil to the high-pressure pump cover gasket (typical)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply a small amount of oil to the high-pressure pump cover gasket.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>(Stripped chassis applications only) - To avoid serious personal injury or possible death,
                        have an assistant help with the installation of the rear cover as it is considerably heavier
                        than the CF chassis version. See
                        <hotlnk xrefid="safety">"Safety Information</hotlnk>."
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="e3001418" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06025.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing the rear cover (CF)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Dowel pins (2)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install rear cover assembly by aligning dowel sleeves on crankcase with rear cover. Push
                    rear cover onto dowel sleeves.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3000114002.5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06070.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Rear cover bolt arrangement (CF)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 35 (8)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="e3001419" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06026.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Torquing the rear cover mounting bolts (typical)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">CF Chassis - Install eight rear cover mounting bolts (M8 x 35) and tighten to the
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_311.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">Standard Torque</hotlnk>. Refer to .
                </para>
                <figure id="f3000114002" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06064.cgm" type="cgm" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Rear cover bolt arrangement (stripped chassis)</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 55 (5)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M10 x 60 (4)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M10 x 70 (2)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft rear oil seal carrier</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 25 (6)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 70 (2)</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <para>Stripped Chassis - Refer to for rear cover bolt pattern. Tighten all bolts to the
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_311.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">Standard Torque</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
